<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-18T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-18T17:00:00-05:00" n="565" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d565">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Moscow/39f: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American
                                    Delegation</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-18T18:00:00-04:00">October
                                    18, 1943—6 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1012. Amdel No. 20. British Embassy has just informed us that a cable
                            received from the Foreign Office states that the British Government have
                            agreed that the statement on “civil affairs for France”<note n="88" xml:id="d565fn88">Conference Document No. 19; for text, see Annex 5
                                to the Secret Protocol signed at Moscow November 1, 1943, <ref target="#pg_760">p. 760</ref>.</note> should be “taken as a
                            basis for discussion in Moscow.” (Your Delam no. 2, October 15.<note n="89" xml:id="d565fn89">Not printed; in it the Secretary requested
                                to be informed when concurrence of the British Government on the
                                statement was received from the British Embassy (740.0011
                                Moscow/29).</note>)</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>[<hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>]</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>